# Frontend Architecture Rules

## Directory responsibilities
- `src/api/` — all `fetch` calls. Never call `fetch` directly from a component or hook.
- `src/hooks/` — stateful logic, side effects, SSE lifecycle.
- `src/components/` — rendering only. No direct API calls or SSE wiring.
- `src/stores/` — shared cross-component state.

## API client pattern
Every function in `src/api/client.js` must follow:
```js
// ✅
const res = await fetch(url, options)
if (!res.ok) throw new Error(`HTTP ${res.status}`)
return res.json()

// ❌ — silent failure, missing check
const res = await fetch(url, options)
return res.json()
```

## Error resilience
Do not remove the root `ErrorBoundary` wrapping the app. Component-level async errors must surface to user state (not just `console.error`).
